In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims October 2010 as National Arts and Humanities Month in the United States. He emphasizes the importance of the arts and humanities in helping people grapple with challenging questions and understand universal truths. The arts are seen as a way to shape our character and remind us of our shared humanity. Additionally, the arts and humanities contribute to the economy, with the non-profit and for-profit arts industries generating billions of dollars annually. The Obama administration is committed to providing arts education to children and has hosted various events at the White House to promote arts and culture. By supporting the arts and humanities, the President believes that America will remain a center of creativity and innovation. The proclamation calls upon the people of the United States to observe National Arts and Humanities Month with appropriate ceremonies, activities, and programs.